zart the Performer brings to life this elusive side of Mozart’s musicianship. Dorian Bandy traces the influence of showmanship on Mozart’s style, showing through detailed analysis and imaginative historical investigation how he conceived his works as a series of dramatic scripts. Mozart the Performer is a book for anyone who wishes to engage more deeply with Mozart’s artistry and legacy and understand why, centuries later, his music still captivates us.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aImprovisation (Music)xHistoryy18th century2DLC. 0aImprovisation (Music)xHistoryy18th century. 0aPianoxPerformancexHistoryy18th century2DLC. 0aPianoxPerformancexHistoryy18th century. 7aMUSIC / General.2bisacsh  aMozart, Wolfgang Amadeus, Composer-performer relationship, Improvisation, Embellishment, Mozart-Da Ponte operas, Historically-informed performance.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226828565423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226828565/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles